{"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.PeakFunction","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.SetIntegral","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.LocallyIntegrable"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L319-L327","name":"tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_continuousOn","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_continuousOn","doc":"If a continuous function `c` realizes its maximum at a unique point `x₀` in a compact set `s`,\nthen the sequence of functions `(c x) ^ n / ∫ (c x) ^ n` is a sequence of peak functions\nconcentrating around `x₀`. Therefore, `∫ (c x) ^ n * g / ∫ (c x) ^ n` converges to `g x₀` if `g` is\ncontinuous on `s`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L297-L312","name":"tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_integrableOn","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_integrableOn","doc":"If a continuous function `c` realizes its maximum at a unique point `x₀` in a compact set `s`,\nthen the sequence of functions `(c x) ^ n / ∫ (c x) ^ n` is a sequence of peak functions\nconcentrating around `x₀`. Therefore, `∫ (c x) ^ n * g / ∫ (c x) ^ n` converges to `g x₀` if `g` is\nintegrable on `s` and continuous at `x₀`.\n\nVersion assuming that `μ` gives positive mass to all open sets.\nFor a less precise but more usable version, see\n`tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_continuousOn`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L198-L285","name":"tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_measure_nhdsWithin_pos","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_measure_nhdsWithin_pos","doc":"If a continuous function `c` realizes its maximum at a unique point `x₀` in a compact set `s`,\nthen the sequence of functions `(c x) ^ n / ∫ (c x) ^ n` is a sequence of peak functions\nconcentrating around `x₀`. Therefore, `∫ (c x) ^ n * g / ∫ (c x) ^ n` converges to `g x₀` if `g` is\nintegrable on `s` and continuous at `x₀`.\n\nVersion assuming that `μ` gives positive mass to all neighborhoods of `x₀` within `s`.\nFor a less precise but more usable version, see\n`tendsto_set_integral_pow_smul_of_unique_maximum_of_isCompact_of_continuousOn`.\n "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L163-L186","name":"tendsto_set_integral_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#tendsto_set_integral_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L88-L158","name":"tendsto_set_integral_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt_aux","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#tendsto_set_integral_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt_aux","doc":"If a sequence of peak functions `φᵢ` converges uniformly to zero away from a point `x₀`, and\n`g` is integrable and continuous at `x₀`, then `∫ φᵢ • g` converges to `x₀`. Auxiliary lemma\nwhere one assumes additionally `g x₀ = 0`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L57-L80","name":"integrableOn_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#integrableOn_peak_smul_of_integrableOn_of_continuousWithinAt","doc":"If a sequence of peak functions `φᵢ` converges uniformly to zero away from a point `x₀`, and\n`g` is integrable and continuous at `x₀`, then `φᵢ • g` is eventually integrable. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.lean#L45-L46","name":"Set.disjoint_sdiff_inter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/PeakFunction.html#Set.disjoint_sdiff_inter","doc":"This lemma exists for finsets, but not for sets currently. porting note: move to\ndata.set.basic after the port. "}]}